# Frontend env vars now live in the REPO-ROOT .env (single source of truth).
# vite.config.ts sets `envDir: '..'`, so Vite reads the root .env for both host
# runs (`npm run dev`/`build`) and Docker (via docker-compose). Do NOT create a
# frontend/.env — it would be ignored by Docker and only shadow the root value
# on host runs (the exact split this consolidation removed).
#
# Set these in the root .env / .env.example instead:
#   VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000
#   VITE_STORE_KEY=mh_pk_madhats_local
